{"TopicId":173612,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Kerbin should have a pole on its poles","CreatedByName":"HeliosPh0enix","CreatedById":181527,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-07T22:05:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"HeliosPh0enix","CreatedById":181527,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-07T22:05:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw another post about a pole inclination, and seeing the word pole got me thinking.\u00A0 What if Kerbin had those red and white striped poles at its north and south pole?\u00A0 They would be interesting navigation targets for missions and would be cool for Kerbal photo ops.\u00A0 Thoughts?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoToH","CreatedById":68428,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-07T23:58:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about Pol poles pole?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003ESorry. I couln\u0027t resist.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HeliosPh0enix","CreatedById":181527,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-08T01:34:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223348310\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523145483\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002268428\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoToH\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, DoToH said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about Pol poles pole?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003ESorry. I couln\u0027t resist.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not think about that!\u00A0 Maybe even have them be something huge, on the scale of the Mun Arch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-08T08:08:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it was something more significant for that beautiful flat landscape, maybe, but simple pole? Just plant the flag, it\u0027s smaller but more visible than a stick.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr, I don\u0027t know, build a relay dish array or a base there.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ARS","CreatedById":168061,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-08T09:17:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPoles can mess up your camera orientation if you abuse it by standing a kerbal directly on it. Watch \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022164481\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Danny2462\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s videos. He\u0027s perhaps the only KSP player who managed to kill a kerbal by using pole (not a stick, an actual planetary pole)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I agree with you that there should be a navigational reference for poles, but as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@The Aziz\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, sticking a flag on poles already accomplished that, not to mention being viewable in tracking station and miles away from it\u0027s general proximity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HeliosPh0enix","CreatedById":181527,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-09T07:14:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223348620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523179049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 hours ago, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPoles can mess up your camera orientation if you abuse it by standing a kerbal directly on it. Watch \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022164481\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Danny2462\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s videos. He\u0027s perhaps the only KSP player who managed to kill a kerbal by using pole (not a stick, an actual planetary pole)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I agree with you that there should be a navigational reference for poles, but as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@The Aziz\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, sticking a flag on poles already accomplished that, not to mention being viewable in tracking station and miles away from it\u0027s general proximity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was thinking that it could be more for community challenges/missions, like drive/fly a vehicle to both poles in whatever way, then have a screenshot of your Kerbal next to the pole marker as a fun way to prove you went there.\u00A0 I don\u0027t know, just a potentially cool idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klesh","CreatedById":110814,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-09T14:19:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223348620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523179049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/8/2018 at 5:17 AM, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe\u0027s perhaps the only KSP player who managed to kill a kerbal by using pole (not a stick, an actual planetary pole)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny player can do this with ease.\u00A0 Just walk into the gaping voids and your kerbal will die.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dZyzH4F.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/dZyzH4F.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-16T00:12:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou should add a poll at the top of this thread so we can vote on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SchweinAero","CreatedById":126909,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-17T09:49:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223355502\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523837557\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 16.4.2018 at 3:12 AM, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou should add a poll at the top of this thread so we can vote on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd as a logical extension, the Pol pole pole poll.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LameLefty","CreatedById":57336,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-17T14:04:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223348620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523179049\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168061\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ARS\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E4\u200E/\u200E8\u200E/\u200E2018 at 4:17 AM, ARS said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPoles can mess up your camera orientation if you abuse it by standing a kerbal directly on it. Watch \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022164481\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/164481-danny2462/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Danny2462\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s videos. He\u0027s perhaps the only KSP player who managed to kill a kerbal by using pole (not a stick, an actual planetary pole)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I agree with you that there should be a navigational reference for poles, but as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@The Aziz\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, sticking a flag on poles already accomplished that, not to mention being viewable in tracking station and miles away from it\u0027s general proximity\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223349731\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022173612\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221523283591\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klesh\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn \u200E4\u200E/\u200E9\u200E/\u200E2018 at 9:19 AM, klesh said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny player can do this with ease.\u00A0 Just walk into the gaping voids and your kerbal will die.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/dZyzH4F.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022dZyzH4F.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/dZyzH4F.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStock Visual Terrain and high-quality terrain settings will prevent any \u0022gaping holes\u0022, at least on Kerbin.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it\u0027s still perfectly possibly to kill a Kerbal by walking directly onto 90.00 N or S.\u00A0 I did it on a recent expedition to the South Pole. Landed on the ice and walked to try to plant a flag directly on the pole. The camera freaked for a second, my Scientist spun around like a rag doll on crack and then disappeared in a tiny little explosion - there were flames and smoke and everything. I sure wish I\u0027d been recording when that happened. I was so astounded I just laughed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo yeah, the game engine treats the axes of spherical bodies as - essentially - mathematical singularities. In Soviet Kerbin, ZERO divides by YOU! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}